this proposal introduces Bellbrook MeshConnect as a smart rural connectivity project aimed to support the digital access in Bellbrook with a low-cost wireless mesh approach. The project will investigate how a community-centric mesh network can be planned, what kind of requirements it should have, what kind of resources it will require, and what kind of risks and constraints might impact implementing such a mesh network.
At this proposal stage, it is not to be claimed that Bellbrook's connectivity problem will be fully solved within the term. Instead, the purpose is to define, justify and plan a feasible project that can demonstrate how a smart mesh networking solution could work in a rural setting. The subsequent sections of the proposal then proceed from background and justification to the problem statement, project objectives, innovative features, scope, requirements, delivery planning, risk management, quality considerations, team roles and tools and resources required.

